      "description": "## Trans-Hub Localizer 0.1.0\n\nInitial public release of Trans-Hub Localizer for Obsidian.\n\n### Highlights\n\n- Localizes supported community plugin names, descriptions, settings, commands, and interface text.\n- Applies published translations at runtime without modifying third-party plugin files or vault notes.\n- Supports selecting one, multiple, or all enabled community plugins.\n- Uses browser-based Trans-Hub account authorization and Obsidian secure storage.\n\n### Release integrity\n\nThis release was built from the tagged source and includes SHA-256 checksums and a GitHub artifact attestation. Download `main.js`, `manifest.json`, and `styles.css`, or use the packaged ZIP for manual installation.\n\n**Full changelog:** https://github.com/SakenW/trans-hub-obsidian-localizer/commits/0.1.0",
